<h2><span class="mw-headline" id="Notes">Notes</span><span class="mw-editsection"><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">[</span><a href="/w/index.php?title=Hispanics_in_the_American_Civil_War&amp;action=edit&amp;section=16" title="Edit section: Notes"><span>edit</span></a><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></span></h2>
<div class="mw-references-wrap"><ol class="references">
<li id="cite_note-14"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="#cite_ref-14">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text"><b>Brevet</b> is a temporary authorization for a person to hold a higher rank which was noted in the officer's title, Example: <b>Brevet Brigadier General</b> Pleasants.</span>
</li>
<li id="cite_note-49"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="#cite_ref-49">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text">Unlike the other military units the <b>European Brigades</b> also had the rank of <b>Third Lieutenant</b></span>
</li>
</ol></div>
